-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Russia Audience Gains, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-07-05T19:23:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-russia-audience-gains-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel rose to the fifth most-watched among Russian viewers 18
years and older in the week to July 1, from seventh a week
before, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, rose to 5.5 percent in the
week to July 1, from 5 percent in the previous week, data
researcher TNS-Global said by e-mail today.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over rose to 6.2 percent in the week to July 1 from 5.6 percent
in the week to June 24, the data show. CTC remained in fifth
place among viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-Global said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched among both
audience categories, the government-controlled Rossiya-1 was the
second-most watched in both segments. Government-controlled
Pervyi Kanal was the third-most watched in both categories and
TNT TV was fourth, the data show.  To contact the reporters on this story:
